# Trivy misconfiguration exceptions (accepted risks with rationale).
# Auto-detected by `trivy config .` (repo root) in local runs and CI.

# AZU-0013 — Key Vault network ACL does not default-deny.
# The Container App consumes DATABASE-URL / GITHUB-TOKEN / ADMIN-PASSWORD /
# DASHBOARD-PASSWORD via runtime Key Vault *references* using its user-assigned
# managed identity over the Key Vault data plane. A `defaultAction: Deny` vault
# is NOT reachable by non-VNet Container Apps (the "trusted Microsoft services"
# bypass does not cover Container Apps secret references), so enabling it here
# would break secret resolution and the running app.
# Compensating controls: RBAC authorization, managed-identity-only access
# (no access policies, no admin keys), soft-delete + purge protection, HTTPS.
# Real fix (tracked separately): add a Key Vault private endpoint + VNet-injected
# Container Apps environment, then set defaultAction to Deny.
AZU-0013

# AZU-0017 — Key Vault secrets have no expiry date.
# These are long-lived operational configuration secrets (DB connection string,
# GitHub PAT, admin/dashboard passwords) without an automated rotation pipeline;
# setting an expiry would cause the app to fail once secrets lapse. Rotation is
# handled operationally (regenerate the PAT / passwords and re-run `azd up`).
AZU-0017
